race.comment: HEALING FREQUENCY (11) was a dominant winner on debut at Pakenham, striking deteriorating conditions there last time when in the market in a stronger race. Forgive that, if she's come through that fine she can bounce back strongly. NAITANUI (8) is lightly raced having won well fresh, okay in a Class 1 last time. He should get a nice run midfield and can figure in the finish. KING INCANTO (1) five-year-old gelding who finished a 2.5 lengths second at Wodonga last time over 1100m. Improver who comes into calculations. QUEEN OF THE SURF (13) is better placed here and can also improve. TASSRON (5) returns from a lay-off. Ran fifth in a jump-out at Flemington. Opened last campaign with a second at this track over 1600m. Include.
